   258→## 0.10.3
   259→
   260→- Improve interactive mode detection ([@andrewsmith])([#183]).
   261→- Refactor parser to fix parsing inconsistencies ([@bbc2])([#170]).
   262→  - Interpret escapes as control characters only in double-quoted strings.
   263→  - Interpret `#` as start of comment only if preceded by whitespace.
   265→## 0.10.2
   266→
   267→- Add type hints and expose them to users ([@qnighy])([#172])
   268→- `load_dotenv` and `dotenv_values` now accept an `encoding` parameter, defaults to `None`
   269→  ([@theskumar])([@earlbread])([#161])
   270→- Fix `str`/`unicode` inconsistency in Python 2: values are always `str` now. ([@bbc2])([#121])
   271→- Fix Unicode error in Python 2, introduced in 0.10.0. ([@bbc2])([#176])
   273→## 0.10.1
   274→- Fix parsing of variable without a value ([@asyncee])([@bbc2])([#158])
   276→## 0.10.0
   277→
   278→- Add support for UTF-8 in unquoted values ([@bbc2])([#148])
   279→- Add support for trailing comments ([@bbc2])([#148])
   280→- Add backslashes support in values ([@bbc2])([#148])
   281→- Add support for newlines in values ([@bbc2])([#148])
   282→- Force environment variables to str with Python2 on Windows ([@greyli])
   283→- Drop Python 3.3 support ([@greyli])
   284→- Fix stderr/-out/-in redirection ([@venthur])
   287→## 0.9.0
   288→
   289→- Add `--version` parameter to cli ([@venthur])
   290→- Enable loading from current directory ([@cjauvin])
   291→- Add 'dotenv run' command for calling arbitrary shell script with .env ([@venthur])
   293→## 0.8.1
   294→
   295→-   Add tests for docs ([@Flimm])
   296→-   Make 'cli' support optional. Use `pip install python-dotenv[cli]`. ([@theskumar])
   298→## 0.8.0
   299→
   300→-   `set_key` and `unset_key` only modified the affected file instead of
   301→    parsing and re-writing file, this causes comments and other file
   302→    entact as it is.
   303→-   Add support for `export` prefix in the line.
   304→-   Internal refractoring ([@theskumar])
   305→-   Allow `load_dotenv` and `dotenv_values` to work with `StringIO())` ([@alanjds])([@theskumar])([#78])
   307→## 0.7.1
   308→
   309→-   Remove hard dependency on iPython ([@theskumar])
   311→## 0.7.0
   312→
   313→-   Add support to override system environment variable via .env.
   314→    ([@milonimrod](https://github.com/milonimrod))
   315→    ([\#63](https://github.com/theskumar/python-dotenv/issues/63))
   316→-   Disable ".env not found" warning by default
   317→    ([@maxkoryukov](https://github.com/maxkoryukov))
   318→    ([\#57](https://github.com/theskumar/python-dotenv/issues/57))
   320→## 0.6.5
   321→
   322→-   Add support for special characters `\`.
   323→    ([@pjona](https://github.com/pjona))
   324→    ([\#60](https://github.com/theskumar/python-dotenv/issues/60))
   326→## 0.6.4
   327→
   328→-   Fix issue with single quotes ([@Flimm])
   329→    ([\#52](https://github.com/theskumar/python-dotenv/issues/52))
   331→## 0.6.3
   332→
   333→-   Handle unicode exception in setup.py
   334→    ([\#46](https://github.com/theskumar/python-dotenv/issues/46))
   336→## 0.6.2
   337→
   338→-   Fix dotenv list command ([@ticosax](https://github.com/ticosax))
   339→-   Add iPython Support
   340→    ([@tillahoffmann](https://github.com/tillahoffmann))
   342→## 0.6.0
   343→
   344→-   Drop support for Python 2.6
   345→-   Handle escaped characters and newlines in quoted values. (Thanks
   346→    [@iameugenejo](https://github.com/iameugenejo))
   347→-   Remove any spaces around unquoted key/value. (Thanks
   348→    [@paulochf](https://github.com/paulochf))
   349→-   Added POSIX variable expansion. (Thanks
   350→    [@hugochinchilla](https://github.com/hugochinchilla))
   352→## 0.5.1
   353→
   354→-   Fix `find_dotenv` - it now start search from the file where this
   355→    function is called from.
   357→## 0.5.0
   358→
   359→-   Add `find_dotenv` method that will try to find a `.env` file.
   360→    (Thanks [@isms](https://github.com/isms))
   362→## 0.4.0
   363→
   364→-   cli: Added `-q/--quote` option to control the behaviour of quotes
   365→    around values in `.env`. (Thanks
   366→    [@hugochinchilla](https://github.com/hugochinchilla)).
   367→-   Improved test coverage.
